Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Desarrolladora Homex, Mexichem Advance

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-29T20:22:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/mexican-stocks-cemex-desarrolladora-homex-mexichem-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index rose 1.1 percent to 36,579.59.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, gained 3.3 percent to 10.15 pesos on speculation
Greece’s efforts to avoid a default will help bolster its
European sales. Cemex gets about a third of its revenue from
 Europe , according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Barclays rated
the shares “equalweight” with its American depositary receipts
receiving a 12-month price target of $9 per share. Cemex ADRs
rose 4.2 percent to $8.63 in New York.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, rose 1.5 percent to 48.69 pesos, its eighth
consecutive advance. Homex shares are undervalued, HSBC analyst
Francisco Suarez Savin said on June 24. Homex trades at 8.8
times 12-month forward earnings, compared to  Mexico ’s IPC index
at 15 times. Shares have risen 13 percent since June 17. “Homex
is a long-term value play,” Suarez said.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM* MM), the largest maker of plastic
pipes in  Latin America , climbed 2.1 percent to 47.39 pesos after
the Mexican chemical producer said it plans a $556 million joint
venture with  Petroleos Mexicanos , the state oil company, to
increase production of vinyl chloride monomer. Mexichem and
Pemex, as the state oil company is known, plan to form a
separate petrochemical company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
